{"questionId":"13102","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>The graph of <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"y = f'\\left( x \\right)\">\n  <mi>y</mi>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <msup>\n    <mi>f</mi>\n    <mo>′</mo>\n  </msup>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mi>x</mi>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span>, 0 ≤ <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"x\">\n  <mi>x</mi>\n</math></span>&nbsp;≤ 5 is shown in the following diagram. The curve intercepts the <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"x\">\n  <mi>x</mi>\n</math></span>-axis at (1, 0) and (4, 0) and has a local minimum at (3, −1).</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><img src=\"__IMG__/3cbb4bffa894dd2e849244395cf6acc76f04a7ec.png\"></p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>The shaded area enclosed by the curve <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"y = f'\\left( x \\right)\">\n  <mi>y</mi>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <msup>\n    <mi>f</mi>\n    <mo>′</mo>\n  </msup>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mi>x</mi>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span>, the <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"x\">\n  <mi>x</mi>\n</math></span>-axis and the <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"y\">\n  <mi>y</mi>\n</math></span>-axis is 0.5.&nbsp;Given that <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"f\\left( 0 \\right) = 3\">\n  <mi>f</mi>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mn>0</mn>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mn>3</mn>\n</math></span>,</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>find the value of&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"f\\left( 1 \\right)\"> <mi>f</mi> <mrow> <mo>(</mo> <mn>1</mn> <mo>)</mo> </mrow> </math></span>.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p>attempt to use definite integral of&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"f'\\left( x \\right)\"> <msup> <mi>f</mi> <mo>′</mo> </msup> <mrow> <mo>(</mo> <mi>x</mi> <mo>)</mo> </mrow> </math></span>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong> (M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\int_0^1 {f'\\left( x \\right){\\text{d}}x}&nbsp; = 0.5\"> <msubsup> <mo>∫</mo> <mn>0</mn> <mn>1</mn> </msubsup> <mrow> <msup> <mi>f</mi> <mo>′</mo> </msup> <mrow> <mo>(</mo> <mi>x</mi> <mo>)</mo> </mrow> <mrow> <mtext>d</mtext> </mrow> <mi>x</mi> </mrow> <mo>=</mo> <mn>0.5</mn> </math></span></p>\n<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"f\\left( 1 \\right) - f\\left( 0 \\right) = 0.5\"> <mi>f</mi> <mrow> <mo>(</mo> <mn>1</mn> <mo>)</mo> </mrow> <mo>−</mo> <mi>f</mi> <mrow> <mo>(</mo> <mn>0</mn> <mo>)</mo> </mrow> <mo>=</mo> <mn>0.5</mn> </math></span>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong> (A1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"f\\left( 1 \\right) = 0.5 + 3\"> <mi>f</mi> <mrow> <mo>(</mo> <mn>1</mn> <mo>)</mo> </mrow> <mo>=</mo> <mn>0.5</mn> <mo>+</mo> <mn>3</mn> </math></span></p>\n<p>= 3.5&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong> A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><em><strong>[3 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"13102","referenceCode":"19M.1.AHL.TZ1.H_8b","subjectId":"50-dp-mathematics-analysis-and-approaches","title":"find the value of f ( 1 ) .","paper":"1","level":"HL","questionNumber":"b","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 3]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 5 —Calculus","Topic 5 —Calculus","SL 5.5—Integration introduction, areas between curve and x axis","Topic 5 —Calculus","SL 5.7—The second derivative"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}